  "text": "Clarified and fixed the eye positioning logic to be consistently center-based. Previously the logic was mixing center-based calculations with some confusion about reference points. Now the eye center is explicitly positioned at 1/3 down the body height, then clamped to stay within body bounds, then converted to top-left SVG coordinates. Also updated mouth positioning to use the clamped eye center position. This makes facial feature positioning much more predictable and balanced across all body sizes.",
